<p><a href="https://assets.documentcloud.org/documents/6960606/Gross-Domestic-Product-GDP-1st-Quarter-2020.txt">Gross Domestic Product (GDP), 1st Quarter 2020 (Text)</a><br /> Roodt blames government for not putting relevant policies in place. “The private sector has been affected by things such as the lockdown and a lack of electricity and a very inefficient state. Yes, there’s more than one player in the economy but I have very little doubt that if they want to blame somebody for the problems that we are experiencing, it must be government for the wrong policies,” explains Roodt. In the video below, Economist Dawie Roodt explains why he blames government policies for regressing GDP: 